The compile failures are all Clippy/format issues, but inspection also exposed a substantive edge hidden by the focused passing tests: an Arm followed by a bad same-tick solution could leave a pending arm edge because the fault event was never merged from a self-loop origin. I’m fixing that as part of D31’s explicit self-loop dominance requirement and adding a regression so a later good solution cannot grant without a fresh Arm.
